<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="434" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1511,2043]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,152,2024]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="434" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1511,1538]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Description</emphasis>
. Length: 
<quantity box="[449,540,1512,1539]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" unit="mm" value="6.8">6.8 mm</quantity>
; Wing: 
<quantity box="[630,720,1512,1539]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" unit="mm" value="6.6">6.6 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[733,853,1511,1538]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">FEMALE</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[868,930,1511,1538]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Head</emphasis>
: dark-blue, shiny, with fine punctuation and black pilosity; face concave, without frontal protuberance. Gena black with short and scarce white pilosity; lunule dark orange and bare (
<figureCitation box="[403,469,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1445,1470]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,586,1434]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cepa simonettii Barahona-Segovia sp. nov., female, head, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3404508/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The space between the eyes (i.e. frons width) is as long as the antenna length. Ocellar triangle in the vertex with pale orange ocelli, occupying approximately the medial 1/3 of vertex and scarcely protuberant (
<figureCitation box="[300,372,1656,1682]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1095,1120]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[177,1410,261,1083]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cepa simonettii Barahona-Segovia sp. nov., female, dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3404510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); occiput reduced laterally with short and black pile. Bare reddish eye. Scape, pedicel and basoflagellomere black. Scape and pedicel in a 1:1 ratio. Basoflagellomere five times longer than the scape and pedicel together. Arista black and bare. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,682,1727,1754]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Thorax</emphasis>
: Mesonotum dark-blue, shiny with short black pilosity (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1394,1728,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1095,1120]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[177,1410,261,1083]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cepa simonettii Barahona-Segovia sp. nov., female, dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3404510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 3). Postpronotum with sparse pilosity. Anterior spiracle with white pilosity. Anterior anepisternum flattened; posterior anepisternum convex with large and dark pilosity dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[822,891,1800,1826]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1999,2024]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1131,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cepa simonettii Barahona-Segovia sp. nov., female, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3404512/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Anepimeron with sparse and continuous pilosity. Katepisternum with short and black pilosity (
<figureCitation box="[717,788,1836,1862]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1999,2024]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1131,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cepa simonettii Barahona-Segovia sp. nov., female, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3404512/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Metasternum with long pilosity. Scutellum with apical marginal sulcus and black erected pilosity (
<figureCitation box="[632,699,1872,1898]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1999,2024]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1131,1988]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cepa simonettii Barahona-Segovia sp. nov., female, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3404512/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[720,774,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Legs</emphasis>
: Coxae, trochanters, and femora dark blue to brown; tibiae, tarsi and claws dark brown. The anterior femora with short black pile; middle and posterior femora with black pile longer than those on the anterior femora. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[618,679,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Wing</emphasis>
(Fig. 4): entirely microtrichose, hyaline, except pterostigma brown pigmented in color. Cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[435,461,1997,2011]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">4+5</subScript>
blunt apically. Crossvein r-m placed in the basal third of cell dm, slightly beyond (more apical) the end of the vein sc. Dorsal and ventral calypters pale; margin with large pale pilosity. Halter entirely black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,261,152,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Abdomen</emphasis>
: blackish brown, stocky, strongly curved ventrally at 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[873,887,152,166]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">rd</superScript>
segment; with fine black pilosity on both tergites and sternites. Fine punctuation in all abdominal tergites; 5 
<superScript attach="left" box="[817,830,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">th</superScript>
tergite light brown and with fine and dense punctuation.
</paragraph>
